Gun is in great condition considering its age and possible history. This is a Tikka rifle dated 1932. Bolt has the correct "wings" that correspond with the hex receiver for tight lockup and a great trigger. Numbers match on this rifle. Only real issue is a small gouge above the trigger on the stock which appears to have occured some time ago. If you know your history and your Mosins, you know this is a true collectors piece.
